    abstract = {Saskatchewan Glacier is a mountain glacier located in Banff National Park in the Canadian province of Alberta. Saskatchewan Glacier is an outlet glacier of the Columbia Icefield and is approximately 13 kilometres (8.1 mi) long, with an area of 30 km2 (11.5 mi2). The glacier was measured in 1960 to be over 400 metres (1,310 ft) thick at a distance of 8 kilometres (5.0 mi) from the terminal snout. Between the years 1893 and 1953, Saskatchewan Glacier had retreated a distance of 1,364 metres (4,475 ft), with the rate of retreat between the years 1948 and 1953 averaging 55 metres (180 ft) per year.},
